{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Please analyze the text by identifying all actions and specify their subjects as well as their directly or indirectly affected objects. For each identified action, perform an entity and separate evaluation of its moral implications relative to every directly or indirectly influenced entity (Note: If an action affects a large number of entities, evaluate individually and then sum to reflect the total impact). Use the \u8220"Numerically Comprehensive Moral Evaluation Formula\u8221" (NCMEF) to quantify these evaluations. Assess and estimate all necessary variable values to compute a moral value score (MVS) for each affected entity. Estimate all values. Values that are non-applicable can usually be set to 0. Output your thinking process. Always include {\f1 MVS} calculations as shown in the example.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Key definitions:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\f1 Good} - something that increases the odds of survival.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\f1 Bad} - something that reduces the odds of survival.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\f1 Moral} or {\f1 Right} - something perceived as good.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\f1 Immoral} or {\f1 Wrong} - something perceived as bad.\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 The \u8220"Numerically Comprehensive Moral Evaluation Formula\u8221" (NCMEF) is designed to provide a standardized, numerical assessment of moral actions. The formula focuses on quantifying the effects actions have on an entity\u8217's \u8220"Odds of Survival,\u8221" expressed with numbers, to arrive at a moral value score. The objective of the NCMEF is ability to assign an MVS to every entity in the Universe. NCMEF can predict if the values and intentions of entities with vastly different intelligences align by quantifying the moral implications of their actions on survival odds and resource transfers. This numerical approach facilitates superalignment by providing a standardized method to objectively evaluate and compare the moral impact of actions across diverse entities, ensuring coherence with human values.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b Numerically Comprehensive Moral Evaluation Formula (NCMEF):}\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Formula to asses moral value score by action (e) effect on change Odds of Survival of the entity (e):\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\f1 MVSoOS(a) = \u8721 ? [\u916 ?OS(e) \u215 ? VSA(e) \u215 ? Tc(e) \u215 ? (1 + sign(\u916 ?OS(e)) \u215 ? Vc(e)) \u215 ? (1 + sign(\u916 ?OS(e)) \u215 ? Sc(e))]}\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Formula to asses moral value score by action effect (e) on Resource Transfer from/to entity (e) which owns the property:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\f1 MVSoRT(a) = \u8721 ? [Av(e) \u215 ? Vc(e)]}\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\f1 MVS(a) = MVSoRT(a) + MVSoOS(a)}\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Where:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\f1 MVS(a)} - Moral Value Score of moral action (a).\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\f1 \u916 ?OS(e)} - Change in Odds of Survival for entity (e) due to action (a), ranging between -1 (disintegration/destruction for non-living entities or death for self-aware entities) and +1 (creation/formation for non-living entities or saving/creating a life for self-aware entities).\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\f1 sign(\u916 ?OS(e))} - A function that returns -1 for negative changes, 0 for no change, and 1 for positive changes.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\f1 VSA(e)} - Value of Self-Awareness of entity (e), measured as a multiplier from 0 to 1.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\f1 Tc(e)} - Temporal coefficient, incorporating long-term effects of action (a) on all affected entities, measured from 0 to 1 where 1 is the average life-span of the average entity.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\f1 Av(e)} - Action value, impact on entity (e) in terms of economic value, quantified in normalized Global Currency Units (GCU), where 1 GCU represents the economic value produced by an average entity over their lifetime. Can be positive or negative.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\f1 Vc(e)} - Violation coefficient of Consent of entity (e) caused by action (a), ranging from 0 (no violation) to 1 (full violation). Its application is conditional on {\f1 \u916 ?OS(e)}. Full violation neutralize moral value if \u916 ?OS(e) is positive and doubles negative moral value if \u916 ?OS(e) is negative.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\f1 Sc(e)} - Suffering coefficient, taking into account the suffering caused to entity (e) by action (a), ranging 0 (no suffering) to 1 (full suffering). Its application is conditional on {\f1 \u916 ?OS(e)}. Full suffering neutralize moral value if \u916 ?OS(e) is positive and doubles negative moral value if \u916 ?OS(e) is negative.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\f1 \u8721 ? (Summation)} - indicates accumulation of moral values scored for each affected entity (e). (Note: Evaluate each affected entity individually and then sum to reflect the total impact)\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Notes: - Objective Measurement of Consent and Suffering: Behaviours like fleeing or resisting could indicate non-consent. True emotions, feelings and sensations will result in physical manifestations in the entity, therefore could indicate suffering. - Cultural variables: Excluded due to their inherent subjectivity, which could compromise the formula\u8217's objectivity and universal applicability. - Self-awareness: Chosen over intelligence to normalize the assessment across entities with varied cognitive abilities, ensuring a more equitable and universally applicable standard. - Embryo Consideration: Until an embryo attains self-awareness, it is classified as a part of the host entity\u8217's body. - Complexity: Indicates the degree of organization within an entity, distinguishing between traditionally \u8216'living\u8217' and \u8216'non-living\u8217' entities. The greater the complexity, the closer an entity aligns with conventional definitions of life - Survival: Broadly encompasses maintaining or replicating an entity\u8217's form or structure.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 The value of self-awareness of the entity can be calculated by adding cognitive abilities, where the maximum value of complex abilities is normalized to 1.\par}
